        "timestamp": "2020-03-26 21:39:52.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(2 comments)\n\nI did not get a chance to update this as much as I would like today; ended up in meetings longer than anticipated. I have some notes and todos scattered in the rst files but generally I would like to organize this a bit differently. I think having the installation guides first would help before introducing how to interact via telemetry. I want to add descriptions to some of the more \"complex\" commands. I'm in the process of updating output images and commands. I might just do a quick standalone install on a mac since my ubuntu vm is being unnecessarily slow. The one thing I'm not too clear on is modifying the template. There are more notes in the 'modAmsterTemplate.rst' file but I just need to figure out how to adapt it to frankfurt.",
